THE Hawks have arrested a suspect who is allegedly connected to a spate of eight bank robberies across Cape Town. The 32-year-old suspect briefly appeared in the Bellville Magistrates Court on Monday, 30 May. Hawks spokeswoman Zinzi Hani said the suspect was arrested in the Khayelitsha area on Friday, 27 May. “It is reported that the accused would walk into a bank and demand cash. The accused has been charged with armed robbery. He is alleged to have robbed Standard Bank and Absa banks in Bellville, Gugulethu, Elsiesriver, Kleinvlei and Kuilsriver areas from the period between November 2021 to March 2022,” Hani said in a statement. She said the accused remains in custody and the matter is remanded to 6 June for legal representation.